a mb mc md me mf mg mh mi eo bj">Authentication is a tricky subject to grasp when you’re just starting out as a software engineer. Fortunately there are lots of libraries out there that can make this task easier… Unfortunately, a lot of the examples are very sandboxed or require you to have more knowledge around security best practices to fully understand what’s going on.</p><p id="f4db" class="pw-post-body-paragraph ln lo ev lp b ft lq lr ls fw lt lu lv lw lx ly lz ma mb mc md me mf mg mh mi eo bj">This article aims to give you an easy to digest example of using NextAuth to:</p><ol class=""><li id="079c" class="ln lo ev lp b ft lq lr ls fw lt lu lv mj lx ly lz mk mb mc md ml mf mg mh mi mm mn mo bj">Securely login to your NextJS Application using an Identity Provider (IdP) of your choosing</li><li id="ca32" class="ln lo ev lp b ft mp lr ls fw mq lu lv mj mr ly lz mk ms mc md ml mt mg mh mi mm mn mo bj">Protect your NextJS API routes with NextAuth</li><li id="6da6" class="ln lo ev lp b ft mp lr ls fw mq lu lv mj mr ly lz mk ms mc md ml mt mg mh mi mm mn mo bj">Use the security token provided by your IdP to integrate with other services</li></ol><p id="8dbb" class="pw-post-body-paragraph ln lo ev lp b ft lq lr ls fw lt lu lv lw lx ly lz ma mb mc md me mf mg mh mi eo bj">We will be using <strong class="lp ew">Azure Active Directory</strong> (Azure AD) as our identity provider, and <strong class="lp ew">AWS AppSync</strong> as the service we want to integrate with.</p><p id="570a" class="pw-post-body-paragraph ln lo ev lp b ft lq lr ls fw lt lu lv lw lx ly lz ma mb mc md me mf mg mh mi eo bj">Before we go any further, let’s talk about Auth.</p><h1 id="934e" class="mu mv ev be mw mx my fv mz na nb fy nc nd ne nf ng nh ni nj nk nl nm nn no np bj">What is an Identity Provider (IdP)?</h1><p id="4686" class="pw-post-body-paragraph ln lo ev lp b ft nq lr ls fw nr lu lv lw ns ly lz ma nt mc md me nu mg mh mi eo bj">An Identity Provider or IdP is a digital identity management service. IdPs allow you to manage users identities, provision roles and permissions, and ultimately determine the resources (integrated services) those users have access to.</p><p id="0535" class="pw-post-body-paragraph ln lo ev lp b ft lq lr ls fw lt lu lv lw lx ly lz ma mb mc md me mf mg mh mi eo bj">For example, if you use Google as an IdP, then your users will be able to login via their Google accounts and gain access to your integrated services without having to create an account or separate login credentials.</p><h1 id="78ca" class="mu mv ev be mw mx my fv mz na nb fy nc nd ne nf ng nh ni nj nk nl nm nn no np bj">How does Authentication work using an IdP?</h1><p id="8ede" class="pw-post-body-paragraph ln lo ev lp b ft nq lr ls fw nr lu lv lw ns ly lz ma nt mc md me nu mg mh mi eo bj">When your users attempts to gain access to a service, the service will redirect the user to the IdP to login. The IdP will verify the user credentials and send some security token back to the service granting them access for a given time period (session).</p><figure class="lb lc ld le lf lg ky kz paragraph-image"><div role="button" tabindex="0" class="lh li hb lj bg lk"><div class="ky kz la"><picture><source srcset="https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:640/format:webp/1*Gxrf8Kg8OS_jZGE1_XXXWQ.png 640w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:720/format:webp/1*Gxrf8Kg8OS_jZGE1_XXXWQ.png 720w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:750/format:webp/1*Gxrf8Kg8OS_jZGE1_XXXWQ.png 750w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:786/format:webp/1*Gxrf8Kg8OS_jZGE1_XXXWQ.png 786w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:828/format:webp/1*Gxrf8Kg8OS_jZGE1_XXXWQ.png 828w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1100/format:webp/1*Gxrf8Kg8OS_jZGE1_XXXWQ.png 1100w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1400/format:webp/1*Gxrf8Kg8OS_jZGE1_XXXWQ.png 1400w" sizes="(min-resolution: 4dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 4) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (min-resolution: 3dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 67vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 3) and (max-width: 700px) 65vw, (min-resolution: 2.5dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2.5) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (min-resolution: 2dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" type="image/webp"><source data-testid="og" srcset="https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:640/1*Gxrf8Kg8OS_jZGE1_XXXWQ.png 640w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:720/1*Gxrf8Kg8OS_jZGE1_XXXWQ.png 720w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:750/1*Gxrf8Kg8OS_jZGE1_XXXWQ.png 750w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:786/1*Gxrf8Kg8OS_jZGE1_XXXWQ.png 786w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:828/1*Gxrf8Kg8OS_jZGE1_XXXWQ.png 828w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1100/1*Gxrf8Kg8OS_jZGE1_XXXWQ.png 1100w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1400/1*Gxrf8Kg8OS_jZGE1_XXXWQ.png 1400w" sizes="(min-resolution: 4dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 4) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (min-resolution: 3dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 67vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 3) and (max-width: 700px) 65vw, (min-resolution: 2.5dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2.5) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (min-resolution: 2dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px"><img alt="" class="bg ll lm c" width="700" height="719" loading="lazy" role="presentation"></picture></div></div></figure><p id="f132" class="pw-post-body-paragraph ln lo ev lp b ft lq lr ls fw lt lu lv lw lx ly lz ma mb mc md me mf mg mh mi eo bj">All subsequent requests during the session can then use that token to verify that the user still has access to the service.</p><h1 id="3e38" class="mu mv ev be mw mx my fv mz na nb fy nc nd ne nf ng nh ni nj nk nl nm nn no np bj">Well, what about authorization?</h1><p id="f164" class="pw-post-body-paragraph ln lo ev lp b ft nq lr ls fw nr lu lv lw ns ly lz ma nt mc md me nu mg mh mi eo bj">You can setup roles and permissions in your IdP and configure your IdP to send <code class="cw nv nw nx ny b">claims</code> with your security token. These claims can contain information such as the user’s type (admin, super user, user, etc…) and groups they are in which you can then use to determine their levels of access for a given resource or application.</p><p id="0d47" class="pw-post-body-paragraph ln lo ev lp b ft lq lr ls fw lt lu lv lw lx ly lz ma mb mc md me mf mg mh mi eo bj">You also use the security toke to authorize user access to third-party services through your application. The flow is very similar to the above, with a few minor changes…</p><figure class="lb lc ld le lf lg ky kz paragraph-image"><div role="button" tabindex="0" class="lh li hb lj bg lk"><div class="ky kz nz"><picture><source srcset="https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:640/format:webp/1*wiJCofLjiHS3TmJXWKvxrA.png 640w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:720/format:webp/1*wiJCofLjiHS3TmJXWKvxrA.png 720w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:750/format:webp/1*wiJCofLjiHS3TmJXWKvxrA.png 750w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:786/format:webp/1*wiJCofLjiHS3TmJXWKvxrA.png 786w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:828/format:webp/1*wiJCofLjiHS3TmJXWKvxrA.png 828w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1100/format:webp/1*wiJCofLjiHS3TmJXWKvxrA.png 1100w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1400/format:webp/1*wiJCofLjiHS3TmJXWKvxrA.png 1400w" sizes="(min-resolution: 4dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 4) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (min-resolution: 3dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 67vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 3) and (max-width: 700px) 65vw, (min-resolution: 2.5dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2.5) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (min-resolution: 2dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" type="image/webp"><source data-testid="og" srcset="https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:640/1*wiJCofLjiHS3TmJXWKvxrA.png 640w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:720/1*wiJCofLjiHS3TmJXWKvxrA.png 720w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:750/1*wiJCofLjiHS3TmJXWKvxrA.png 750w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:786/1*wiJCofLjiHS3TmJXWKvxrA.png 786w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:828/1*wiJCofLjiHS3TmJXWKvxrA.png 828w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1100/1*wiJCofLjiHS3TmJXWKvxrA.png 1100w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1400/1*wiJCofLjiHS3TmJXWKvxrA.png 1400w" sizes="(min-resolution: 4dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 4) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (min-resolution: 3dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 67vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 3) and (max-width: 700px) 65vw, (min-resolution: 2.5dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2.5) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (min-resolution: 2dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px"><img alt="" class="bg ll lm c" width="700" height="780" loading="lazy" role="presentation"></picture></div></div></figure><p id="c101" class="pw-post-body-paragraph ln lo ev lp b ft lq lr ls fw lt lu lv lw lx ly lz ma mb mc md me mf mg mh mi eo bj">Here we see that the user requested access to a third-party service. The main service sends the security token to the third-party service which then forwards it on to the IdP to authenticate the user.</p><p id="1eea" class="pw-post-body-paragraph ln lo ev lp b ft lq lr ls fw lt lu lv lw lx ly lz ma mb mc md me mf mg mh mi eo bj">The third-party service may also use the claims in the security token to parse roles and groups and act accordingly. A good example of this would be checking that a user is an admin when requesting data marked as <code class="cw nv nw nx ny b">admin only</code> in the third-party service.</p><figure class="lb lc ld le 